metadata.name: Coma
metadata.description:
Death is being reborn 
Fully awake into the memories 
Of our complete life 

Walking again these same moments
Knowing where each rain drop will land 

At first we scream at ourselves
“Let her go!” 
And of course we cannot hear

Now we linger 
Notice the wind blow her hair
Notice she averts her eyes
Notice we aren’t noticing 

Now we let the vase fall
Again and again and again 
Flowers and water spill everywhere

all exquisite moments unfold
and finally we are free. 

Beautiful Zach Braiker poem for this art

13 Seconds loop
60 fps
